node.title: Police now treating case of man missing in remote south-west Queensland as 'suspicious'
node.alt: An Indigenous man in a blue polo shirt and black trousers stands with his hands behind his back.
node.description: Twenty-seven-year-old Jeremiah RiversÂ was last seen walking away from the group he was camping with near Wippo Creek, south of Noccundra, on the morning of October 18.
node.content: ["Police say the case of Jeremiah Rivers, who has been missing in remote south-west Queensland for nearly three weeks, is now being treated as suspicious.", "The 27-year-old, who is also known as \"Jayo\", was last seen walking away from the group he was camping with near Wippo Creek, south of Noccundra, on the morning of October 18.", "A police and SES search for Mr Rivers was called off after five days.", "A spokesperson for the Queensland Police Service said authorities were now treating his disappearance as suspicious, \"after a number of inquiries\".", "\"A number of officers are involved including [Criminal Investigation Branch] and specialist police,\" the spokesperson said.", "Police are expected to provide further information at a press conference this afternoon.", "More to come."]
